{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionEmotion is an essential part of our daily lives.",
    "Many scholars, particularly in human-computer interaction (HCI), aim to quantify various aspects of emotions.",
    "They use measurements of emotion to improve designs, human interaction, decision making, and many more [151], e.g., using speech to asses learners in online learning to study how they respond to a course [5].",
    "Human-computer interaction is one of such domains.",
    "Computers can make better decisions with the use of emotion identification to help users [5].Moreover, brainwave signals can be used to detect players' emotions while playing a game to predict their affective states."
  ]
}